  1. Write a java program using class to solve the following series.

    Y=1+(2/3!)+(3/4!)+.......

    CODE:

    class Series{


    public static void main(String[] args){ if(args.length==0){

    System.out.println("Input Number of Terms"); return;

    }

    int numberTerms=Integer.parseInt(args[0]); double sum = 1.0;

    long factorial = 1;

    for(int i=2;i<=numberTerms;i++){ factorial*=(i+2);

    double term=(double)i/factorial; sum+=term;

    }

    System.out.println("Sum of the series Y = " + sum);

    }}

    OUTPUT:

    D:\SYCS45>javac Series.java

    D:\SYCS45>Java Series 5

    Sum of the series Y = 1.281547619047619

  2. Write a java program to sort a given array. CODE:

    class BubbleSort {

    public void sort(int[] array) { int n = array.length;

    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

    for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) { if (array[j] > array[j + 1]) {

    int temp = array[j]; array[j] = array[j + 1]; array[j + 1] = temp;

    }}}}


    public void printArray(int[] array) { int n = array.length;

    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) { System.out.print(array[i] + " ");

    }System.out.println();

    }}

    class MainClass {

    public static void main(String[] args) { BubbleSort bubbleSort = new BubbleSort(); int[] array = {7,8,3,1,2}; System.out.println("Original array:"); bubbleSort.printArray(array); bubbleSort.sort(array); System.out.println("Sorted array:"); bubbleSort.printArray(array);

    }}


    OUTPUT:

  3. Write a java program to input telephone number and number of calls. Calculate and display the bill amount which include a fixed rent of Rs. 400. The first 150 calls are free with excess calls are charged 80 paisa each.

    CODE:

    class TelephoneBill { long phoneNumber; int numberOfCalls; double billAmount;


    void inputDetails() { phoneNumber = 1234567890;

    numberOfCalls = 200;

    }


    void calculateBill() { double callCharges = 0.0;

    if (numberOfCalls > 150) {

    callCharges = (numberOfCalls - 150) * 0.8;

    }

    billAmount = 400 + callCharges;

    }


    void displayBill() {

    System.out.println("Phone Number: " + phoneNumber); System.out.println("Number of Calls: " + numberOfCalls); System.out.println("Bill Amount: Rs. " + billAmount);

    }}

    class Bill {

    public static void main(String[] args) { TelephoneBill bill = new TelephoneBill(); bill.inputDetails();

    bill.calculateBill(); bill.displayBill();

    }

    }


    OUTPUT:

    D:\SYCS45>javac Bill.java


    D:\SYCS45>java Bill

    Phone Number: 1234567890 Number of Calls: 200

    Bill Amount: Rs. 440.0

    return weight < 50 && height > 170;

    }


    class CalculationHW {

    public static void main(String[] args) { Person[] people = new Person[10]; people[0] = new Person(175, 45); people[1] = new Person(168, 60); people[2] = new Person(180, 48); people[3] = new Person(172, 52); people[4] = new Person(165, 49); people[5] = new Person(178, 42); people[6] = new Person(160, 55); people[7] = new Person(173, 47); people[8] = new Person(167, 58); people[9] = new Person(171, 43);


    int count = 0;

    for (Person person : people) { if (person.isEligible()) {

    count++;

    }

    }

    }

    }

  1. Write a java program to reverse the digits of a number. Number is passed using the method. Code:

    import java.util.Scanner; public class ReverseNumber {

    public static int reverse(int num) { int reversed = 0;

    while (num != 0) { int digit = num % 10;

    reversed = reversed * 10 + digit; num /= 10;}

    return reversed;}

    public static void main(String[] args) {

    Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in); System.out.print("Enter a number to reverse: "); int number = scanner.nextInt();

    int reversedNumber = reverse(number); System.out.println("The original number is: " + number);

    System.out.println("The reversed number is: " + reversedNumber); scanner.close(); }}

    Output:

    C:\Users\admin\Desktop\java Practical>java ReverseNumber Enter a number to reverse: 836473

    The original number is: 836473 The reversed number is: 374638

Q1] Write a java program that demonstrate the usage of Inheritance by using suitable class: A class called Inher_1 that defines an array containing numbers of int type. A class called Inher_2 inherits Inher_1. It defines a method called menu(k) to display menu as numbers from Inher_1,sum of numbers, average of numbers and maximum numbers. A class InherDemo defines main () method and an object defined for Inher_2. Invoke menu (k) method to get appropriate results by passing different values of k.

import java.util.Arrays; import java.util.Collections; class Inher_1{

int arr[]={6,8,10,11,26,33,34,45,62};

}

class Inher_2 extends Inher_1{ int i;

int sum=0; int max;

void menu(int k){ switch(k){

case 1:

System.out.println("Numbers in the array are: "); for(i=0;i<arr.length;i++){

System.out.print(" "+arr[i]);

}

System.out.println(); break;

case 2:

System.out.println("Addition of the numbers in the array is: "); for(i=0;i<arr.length;i++){

sum=sum+arr[i];

}

System.out.println(sum); break;

case 3:

System.out.println("Average of the numbers in the array is: "); for(i=0;i<arr.length;i++){

sum=sum+arr[i];

}

System.out.println(sum/ arr.length); break;

case 4:

System.out.println("Maximum number in the array is: "); for(i=0;i<arr.length;i++){

max=Collections.max(Arrays.asList(arr[i]));

}

System.out.println(max); break;

default:

System.out.println("Invalid Input");

}

}

}

public class InherDemo {

public static void main(String args[]) { Inher_2 obj=new Inher_2(); if(args.length!=0) {

int choice = Integer.parseInt(args[0]); obj.menu(choice);

}

else

System.out.println("Arguments not passed"); System.out.println("Finished !!!");

}

}

InterDemo:

class InterCall implements Inter { public void show(int x) {

System.out.println("Square of " + x + " = " + (x * x)); System.out.println("Max= " + max);

Q3 Write a java program to demonstrate synchronization of threads Code:

class Callme {

synchronized void call(String msg) { System.out.print("[" + msg);

try { Thread.sleep(1000);

} catch(InterruptedException e) { System.out.println("Interrupted");

}

System.out.println("]");

}

}

class Caller implements Runnable { String msg;

Callme target; Thread t;

public Caller(Callme targ, String s) { target = targ;

msg = s;

t = new Thread(this); t.start();

}

public void run() { target.call(msg);

}

}

public class sync {

public static void main(String args[]) { Callme target = new Callme();

Caller ob1 = new Caller(target, "Hello");

Caller ob2 = new Caller(target, "Synchronized"); Caller ob3 = new Caller(target, "World");

try { ob1.t.join();

ob2.t.join();

ob3.t.join();

} catch(InterruptedException e) { System.out.println("Interrupted");

}

}

}

import java.io.*; import java.net.*; public class server {

public static void main(String args[]) { try {

ServerSocket serverSocket = new ServerSocket(5000); System.out.println("Server started. Waiting for a client..."); Socket socket = serverSocket.accept(); System.out.println("Client connected!");

InputStream input = socket.getInputStream();

BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(input)); OutputStream output = socket.getOutputStream();

PrintWriter writer = new PrintWriter(output, true); String message = reader.readLine(); System.out.println("Received from client: " + message); writer.println("Hello from the server!");

socket.close(); serverSocket.close();

System.out.println("Server closed.");

} catch (IOException e) { System.out.println("Exception!!!");;

}

}

}

private void jButton1ActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt) { Date inputDate = jDateChooser1.getDate();

DateTimeFormatter outputFormatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("yyyy-MM-dd");


LocalDate dob = null; try {

LocalDate localDate = inputDate.toInstant().atZone(ZoneId.systemDefault()).toLocalDate();


String formattedDate = localDate.format(outputFormatter); dob = LocalDate.parse(formattedDate, outputFormatter);


} catch (Exception e) {

JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Please enter Date of Birth in the correct format (yyyy-MM-dd).", "Date Format Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);

return;

}


if (dob == null) {

JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Date of Birth is not valid.", "Date Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);

return;

}


LocalDate currentDate = LocalDate.now();

int currentAge = Period.between(dob, currentDate).getYears(); if (currentAge<21||currentAge>60) {

JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Customer age must be between 21 and 60 years.", "Age Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);

return;

}

// Calculate years remaining until age 60 int yearsRemaining = 60 - currentAge;


String selectedAmount = (String)jComboBox1.getSelectedItem();

// Convert selected investment amount to a double

double investmentAmount = Double.parseDouble(selectedAmount);


// Calculate premium (example calculation: investment amount / years remaining) double premium = investmentAmount / yearsRemaining;


jLabel6.setText(""+premium);

}

    String password = "SYCS28";


    int depno;

    scanner.nextLine();

    System.out.print("Enter Department Location: "); location = scanner.nextLine();

    try {

    Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");

    Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, password);


    String query = "INSERT INTO department (dept_no, dept_name, location) VALUES (?, ?, ?)";

    PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(query);


    statement.setInt(1, depno); statement.setString(2, deptname); statement.setString(3, location);

    int rowsInserted = statement.executeUpdate(); if (rowsInserted > 0) {

    } catch (SQLException e) { System.out.println("Database error occurred!"); e.printStackTrace();

    } finally { scanner.close();

    }

    }

package com;


import javax.jws.WebService; import javax.jws.WebMethod; import javax.jws.WebParam;


@WebService(serviceName = "TempConvertor") public class TempConvertor {


@WebMethod(operationName = "CtoF")

public double CtoF(@WebParam(name = "C") double C) { double f = C * 1.8 + 32;

return f;

}

@WebMethod(operationName = "FtoC")

public double FtoC(@WebParam(name = "F") double F) { double C = (F - 32) / 1.8;

return C;

}

}
